# Remote Collaboration & Development Plan

## Goal Description
To establish a robust workflow for collaborating with a teammate who has physical access to the BeagleBone. This involves setting up remote access via Tailscale, defining a strict API contract for data exchange, and enhancing the local simulation environment (`beaglebone_vm.py`) to mirror real hardware behavior.

## User Review Required
> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Tailscale Installation**: The teammate needs to be willing/able to install Tailscale on the BeagleBone and join the shared Tailnet.

## Proposed Changes

### Documentation
#### [NEW] [remote-collaboration.md](file:///d:/Developpement/Projets/WEB/Virtual Fencing & Health Monitoring System/docs/remote-collaboration.md)
- **Tailscale Setup**: Step-by-step guide for the teammate to install and configure Tailscale.
- **Microcontroller-BeagleBone Interface**: Define the serial/I2C communication protocol.
- **Git Workflow**: Guidelines for pushing/pulling code to the device.

#### [NEW] [api-contract.md](file:///d:/Developpement/Projets/WEB/Virtual Fencing & Health Monitoring System/docs/api-contract.md)
- **JSON Schema**: Strict definition of the data payload sent from BeagleBone to Backend.
- **Endpoints**: Documentation of REST API endpoints (`POST /api/imu-activity`, etc.).

### Simulation
#### [MODIFY] [beaglebone_vm.py](file:///d:/Developpement/Projets/WEB/Virtual Fencing & Health Monitoring System/beaglebone_vm.py)
- **Update Data Structure**: Align the generated fake data exactly with the new `api-contract.md`.
- **Enhanced Behavior**: Add more realistic random walks and activity states (Grazing, Ruminating, etc.) to mimic real cattle behavior better, aiding local frontend/backend dev.

## Verification Plan

### Manual Verification
- **Documentation Review**: User and Teammate review the guides.
- **Simulation Test**: Run `beaglebone_vm.py` and verify it sends data to the local backend that matches the schema.
- **Connectivity Test**: (Once teammate sets up Tailscale) SSH into the device.
